[{'text': 'Bell Tone', 'start': 0.01, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'Bell Tone', 'start': 4.03, 'duration': 3.02}, {'text': 'Music', 'start': 7.07, 'duration': 3.03}, {'text': 'Narrator: When we look up at the sun from Earth, it seems calm and unchanging.', 'start': 10.12, 'duration': 3.09}, {'text': 'The truth is quite different.', 'start': 13.23, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'Music', 'start': 17.26, 'duration': 4.04}, {'text': 'Music', 'start': 21.32, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'Music', 'start': 25.34, 'duration': 4.08}, {'text': 'In addition to these abrupt changes in activity, the sun also has long', 'start': 29.44, 'duration': 4.07}, {'text': 'term, more regular pattern of change. This pattern is called the sunspot', 'start': 33.53, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'cycle and a single cycle lasts for about 11 years, although it can be as short', 'start': 37.56, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'as 8 or as long as 14 and it can vary dramatically in intensity.', 'start': 41.6, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'During one cycle, the number of sunspots, a good indicator of ', 'start': 45.64, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'solar activity, goes from low to high and back down to low.', 'start': 49.66, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'Solar minimum represents a time when sunspot numbers are relatively low,', 'start': 53.68, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'and solar maximum represents a period when sunspot numbers are relatively high.', 'start': 57.7, 'duration': 4.07}, {'text': 'During this cycle, the location of the sunspots also', 'start': 61.79, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'changes. They are at middle latitudes during solar maximum, and move', 'start': 65.81, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'closer to the equator as the sun approaches solar minimum. At solar minimum,', 'start': 69.83, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'there are sometimes no sunspots to observe. At solar maximum there can be many', 'start': 73.85, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'at the same time. The number of sunspots is important', 'start': 77.88, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'because sunspots are the visual markers of where powerful magnetic fields have emerged', 'start': 81.92, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': "from the sun's interior. These magnetic fields power solar flares and ", 'start': 85.96, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'coronal mass ejections, which can affect Earth and other objects in the solar system.', 'start': 89.98, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'As the sunspots increase, so does the frequency and severity', 'start': 94.02, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': "of flares and CMEs. The sun's 11-year", 'start': 98.04, 'duration': 4.07}, {'text': 'cycle is a symptom of a longer, 22-year-cycle called the solar cycle,', 'start': 102.13, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': "or Hale Cycle, which affects the sun's magnetic fields.", 'start': 106.16, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': "Every 11 years, the sun's poles flip--north becomes south and south", 'start': 110.19, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'becomes north, so every 22 years, the poles return to the position', 'start': 114.22, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'where they started the cycle. The flip is due to the complex movement of', 'start': 118.25, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'magnetic fields inside the sun that are constantly stretching, twisting, and ', 'start': 122.29, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': "crossing as solar material bubbles up from the sun's core. But the exact", 'start': 126.33, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'pattern of movements is not yet mapped out. Because the sunspot', 'start': 130.37, 'duration': 4.1}, {'text': 'cycle follows a similar pattern regardless of the orientation of the poles,', 'start': 134.49, 'duration': 4.04}, {'text': 'it only takes half as long as the solar cycle. The two cycles are different,', 'start': 138.55, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'but the 11-year sunspot cycle is often referred to as the solar cycle,', 'start': 142.58, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'which can be a little confusing. Right now the', 'start': 146.6, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': 'sun is approaching solar maximum, so flares and CMEs are more common than', 'start': 150.63, 'duration': 4.08}, {'text': 'they were a few years ago. This cycle may peak in 2013, or', 'start': 154.73, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'early 2014, and should reach its minimum around 2020', 'start': 158.75, 'duration': 4.0}, {'text': 'although predictions about the sun are still uncertain. The slower', 'start': 162.77, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'than expected progress of this sunspot cycle has led some to speculate', 'start': 166.81, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'that the next sunspot cycle might be very minimal, with few sunspots even at', 'start': 170.85, 'duration': 4.14}, {'text': 'solar maximum. It is still far too early to know, but even if this is', 'start': 175.01, 'duration': 4.01}, {'text': "the case, it has happened before and isn't something to worry about, it just means", 'start': 179.04, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'that the sun would briefly be a little closer to the unchanging orb it looks like from', 'start': 183.08, 'duration': 4.02}, {'text': 'the ground.', 'start': 187.12, 'duration': 1.0}, {'text': 'Music', 'start': 188.14, 'duration': 4.04}, {'text': 'Beeping', 'start': 192.2, 'duration': 13.1}]

between the ball joint bolt and the front', 'start': 10.76, 'duration': 3.85}, {'text': 'control arm bolt.
Here is what the measures should be.', 'start': 14.61, 'duration': 3.35}, {'text': 'When doing this, the car needs to have a full
tank of gas and be sitting on flat, level ground.', 'start': 17.96, 'duration': 4.58}, {'text': 'The measurements should be taken with a surface gauge like this one.', 'start': 22.7, 'duration': 3.96}, {'text': 'I took the shade tree method of just using a tape measure.', 'start': 26.66, 'duration': 3.28}, {'text': 'First remove the ball joint bolt.', 'start': 30.14, 'duration': 4.46}, {'text': 'Separate the ball joint from the steering knuckle.', 'start': 40.52, 'duration': 3.28}, {'text': 'Remove the front control arm bolt.', 'start': 47.22, 'duration': 3.58}, {'text': 'Remove the rear control arm bolt.', 'start': 70.2, 'duration': 4.18}, {'text': 'Now remove the control arm.', 'start': 83.64, 'duration': 2.76}, {'text': 'Insert the new control arm starting with the
rear bushing and hand tighten the bolt.', 'start': 87.049, 'duration': 6.791}, {'text': 'With the help of a floor jack, try to align
the holes of the front bushing.', 'start': 100.96, 'duration': 7.0}, {'text': 'Hand tighten the front control arm bolt.', 'start': 109.24, 'duration': 4.12}, {'text': 'Now try to get the ball joint back into the steering knuckle. I used a pry bar to guide the joint in.', 'start': 113.36, 'duration': 7.36}, {'text': 'Insert the ball joint bolt and hand tighten
the nut.', 'start': 126.32, 'duration': 4.68}, {'text': 'Using a floor jack, push up on the control
arm until you are within the acceptable range', 'start': 131.009, 'duration': 3.551}, {'text': 'of the front ride height shown at the beginning
of the video.', 'start': 134.56, 'duration': 2.36}, {'text': 'Once positioned correctly, torque the bolts
to the following specs.', 'start': 137.67, 'duration': 3.82}, {'text': "The reason this is done is to make sure the
bushings aren't twisted when the car is resting", 'start': 144.64, 'duration': 3.09}, {'text': "in it's natural position. Otherwise the bushings
will fail prematurely.", 'start': 147.73, 'duration': 5.369}, {'text': "On the driver's side, I ran into a problem
with the control arm.", 'start': 153.099, 'duration': 2.691}, {'text': "It wasn't made to spec and I couldn't pivot
the arm low enough to get the ball joint to", 'start': 155.79, 'duration': 4.19}, {'text': 'clear the steering knuckle.
I needed to cut away parts of the control', 'start': 159.98, 'duration': 3.66}, {'text': 'arm that was making contact with the frame.', 'start': 163.64, 'duration': 2.24}, {'text': 'I did a little bit of cutting while the arm
was still in.', 'start': 167.14, 'duration': 3.08}, {'text': 'It did help to undo the front bolt and swing
